							 <h1>RULES AND REGULATIONS</h1>
								<ol>
											<li>The tournaments on various games and sports will be conducted in accordance with the latest rules followed in the international federations of respective games.</li>
											<li>Officials for the matches will be appointed by the organizing committee.</li>
											<li>Teams must send their entries on or before 8th January 2014.</li>
											<li>Registration can be done in either of the two ways-<br>
													1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Online registration<br>
													2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Registration at the registration desk at NIT Campus</li>
											<li>Confirmation of entry would be sent either by email or a telephone call to the representative.</li>
											<li>Colleges willing to register must submit the letter of authorisation from the head of the institute mentioning the names of the participants, at the time of registration.</li>
											<li>Team members must produce their identity cards issued by their institutes at the registration desk at the time of reporting. Failure in doing so will result in disqualification of the team/player.</li>
											<li>All players must be in their proper sports uniform and kits.</li>
											<li>Decision of the umpires/arbiters will be final and binding upon all.</li>
											<li>Any misconduct during the event will lead to disqualification of the team.</li>
											<li>Every team should report half an hour before the scheduled match. Reporting after 15 minutes of the commencement of the match will lead to disqualification of the team.</li>
											<li>Online registration of all events started from 30th November 2014 and the registration desk at NIT would start functioning from 11th January 2014. The team has to report at NIT Rourkela on or before 12th January 2014.</li>
											<li>For more information visit our website- <a href="index.html" target="_blank">sportsfiesta.nitrkl.ac.in</a></li>
								</ol>
								
								
